# .gitignore - ADSP-SC598 Yocto build harness
# ============================================================================
# Tracked = the build tooling you maintain by hand:
#   Makefile, config.mk, bin/, overlays/, and the app sources under src/apps/.
# Everything ignored below is fetched (`make init`/`make fetch`), generated
# (`make apps`/`make image`/`make update-tooling`), or a build artifact - all
# re-creatable, none belongs in git.
# ============================================================================

# --- Fetched / generated under src/ -----------------------------------------
# src/apps/ is the ONLY hand-written tree under src/. Everything else there is
# the ADI BSP and build state:
#   src/.repo, src/bin            - `make init`  (repo metadata + launcher)
#   src/sources, src/downloads,
#   src/setup-environment         - `make fetch` (repo sync)
#   src/layers                    - `make apps`  (generated meta-custom-apps)
#   src/<BUILDDIR>, e.g. src/build - bitbake build tree
# So: ignore everything under src/ except src/apps/.
/src/*
!/src/apps/

# --- src/apps/ : hand-written app sources are TRACKED ------------------------
# app.yaml, the src/ tree, LICENSE, config/ + service/ files, and prebuilt
# binaries dropped in <app>/binary/ are inputs `make apps` consumes - tracked.
# Cross-compilation runs in the bitbake WORKDIR, never under src/apps, so the
# only artifacts that land here come from compiling an app in-tree:
/src/apps/**/build/
/src/apps/**/*.o
/src/apps/**/*.a
/src/apps/**/*.so
/src/apps/**/*.elf
/src/apps/**/*.bin
/src/apps/**/*.map
# Prebuilt tarballs in <app>/binary/ are not committed (they bloat history; a
# kind=prebuilt-tarball app using a file:// URL then won't `make apps` from a
# fresh clone - host it remotely with a sha256). Bare prebuilt binaries stay
# tracked, since file:// builds need them present locally.
/src/apps/*/binary/*.tar.gz
# In-tree host-compiled binaries are extension-less and share the app's name,
# so a glob can't catch them; each app ignores its own via a committed
# src/apps/<name>/src/.gitignore that `make new-app` generates.

# --- Generated output at the project root -----------------------------------
# images/  : build outputs (wic.gz, sdcard.img) from `make image` / `make sdcard`
# tooling/ : self-extracting tooling archive from `make update-tooling`
/images/
/tooling/

# --- editor / OS noise ------------------------------------------------------
*~
*.sw?
.DS_Store
